{"TopicId":180944,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Stratolaunch / Horizontal Pegasus launch.","CreatedByName":"Patrick C","CreatedById":194287,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-12-28T05:08:03Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Patrick C","CreatedById":194287,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-12-28T05:08:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think this is the right forum for this question, I\u0027ve looked else where but have not found this answer.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoes Kerbal allow horizontal launches from different altitudes on earth ? or just launch pads ?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf not can I raise a launch pad to a 50,000 ft mountain side (though it would be stationary) ? I\u0027m interested in the academic math and physics involved.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSpecifically how big (mass) a rocket would need to be to put a 3 kg payload in LEO.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTY, Patrick\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-12-28T05:10:28Z\u0022 title=\u002212/28/2018 05:10  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 28, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Patrick C\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003Eforgot abit\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"0111narwhalz","CreatedById":110660,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-12-28T06:27:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEasy way to do it is probably just to stick your rocket on another rocket, and tune the apoapsis upon ascent before jettisoning it and proceeding with your real rocket.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStarting a plane at altitude is likely to result in problems, because many planes in KSP require ram compression to get enough intake air, especially at altitude\u2014some even require it on the ground. Even if the engines \u003Cem\u003Eare\u003C/em\u003E able to start, you\u0027ll have problems getting enough air under your wings\u2014the only reason planes can fly at the low pressures of the upper atmosphere is because of their great speed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLaunching a rocket from altitude is probably feasable\u2014however, very little of what is gained from Stratolaunch is due to altitude. Much more important is the \u0022free\u0022 velocity. This is not accounted for in a static launch from high altitude.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFinally, 3kg is \u003Cem\u003Ereally\u003C/em\u003E light for anything in KSP. You\u0027re going to need either a sounding rocket pack or Tweakscale to examine that regime with any kind of accuracy.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Patrick C","CreatedById":194287,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-12-28T06:32:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nis \u0022tweakscale\u0022 an add on pack type thing ? i dont own KSP yet.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Scotius","CreatedById":57622,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-12-28T08:04:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223512218\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022180944\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221545978775\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022194287\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Patrick C\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Patrick C said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nis \u0022tweakscale\u0022 an add on pack type thing ? i dont own KSP yet.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo. It is a module that let you manipulate the size of existing parts - it doesn\u0027t add any part of its own. But you can make those parts bigger or smaller according to needs.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DDE","CreatedById":146349,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-12-28T08:11:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223512191\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022180944\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221545973684\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022194287\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Patrick C\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, Patrick C said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoes\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E Kerbal allow horizontal launches from different altitudes on earth ? or just launch pads ?\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStock KSP has a single vertical launchpad at near sea level. Furthermore, the reduced scale of everything (Kerbin has a radius of 640 km, yet 1 g gravity) mucks up any attempt to mode real life.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-12-28T08:12:27Z\u0022 title=\u002212/28/2018 08:12  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 28, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by DDE\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"hms_warrior","CreatedById":142205,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-12-28T08:14:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere are, however, a lot of mods( wich are free) that allow you to get a better simulation. Like a Earth sized Kerbin for example.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Xd the great","CreatedById":188222,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-12-28T11:35:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI recommend the following mods:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Real Solar System (mod)\u0022\u003ERSS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u002B\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Realism Overhaul (mod)\u0022\u003ERO\u003C/abbr\u003E, \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aerospace Research (mod)\u0022\u003EFAR\u003C/abbr\u003E, Real Scale Boosters, and some realistic plane packs.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Green Baron","CreatedById":107381,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-12-28T12:44:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWelcome, \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/194287-patrick-c/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022194287\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/194287-patrick-c/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Patrick C\u003C/a\u003E, to the forum \u003Cspan\u003E:-)\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBesides all the other valuable info, mods like Kerbinside offer launch sites at different places. Well, not at 50.000ft amsl because such a mountain does not exist. Get the game and try it out. You will not regret it :-)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n- you can launch horizontally with a space plane. Which is somewhat advanced.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n- math and physics: a good place to start is the wiki. Academic math and physics, well, an archaeologist can play it ...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n- mass fraction of payload is higher than irl. It is hard to give numbers, but ... 10% ? When you are through with the wiki and things like the rocket equation you will calculate the abilities of your designs on your own or use mods to display the numbers while you build.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTo start: dive into calculation of \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Delta-V\u0022\u003EdV\u003C/abbr\u003E (Delta-V), the ability of a rocket to change its speed by a certain amount of m/s. To reach a low orbit outside of Kerbin\u0027s atmosphere you need ~3.3km/s (if i recall that right ...). For a real world earth that\u0027ll be around 8km/s. If you don\u0027t mess up the ascent too much, that is.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHope i don\u0027t get to big a correction now \u003Cspan\u003E:-)\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-12-28T12:46:37Z\u0022 title=\u002212/28/2018 12:46  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 28, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Green Baron\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"winged","CreatedById":143617,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-12-28T13:22:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223512217\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022180944\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221545978446\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022110660\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u00220111narwhalz\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, 0111narwhalz said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFinally, 3kg is \u003Cem\u003Ereally\u003C/em\u003E light for anything in KSP. You\u0027re going to need either a sounding rocket pack or Tweakscale to examine that regime with any kind of accuracy.\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWith \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Realism Overhaul (mod)\u0022\u003ERO\u003C/abbr\u003E suite of mods you can launch even 0,25 kg payload to orbit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Patrick C","CreatedById":194287,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-12-28T21:22:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes I want an earth like approximation. alright after looking at other programs like \u0022orbiter\u0022 ill buy Kerbal. Ive been watching \u0022Everyday Astronaut\u0022 and want to play with some \u0022tyrannical\u0022 physics.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIll try to figure it out so ill keep posting if you\u0027ll all keep helping.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Patrick C","CreatedById":194287,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-12-28T22:41:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI killed Jeb.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nightside","CreatedById":150244,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-12-29T01:56:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223512530\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022180944\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221546036903\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022194287\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Patrick C\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, Patrick C said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI killed Jeb.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCome for the physics stay for the crashes !\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Xd the great","CreatedById":188222,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-12-29T02:07:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223512530\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022180944\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221546036903\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022194287\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Patrick C\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, Patrick C said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ip